Her lectures are quite hard to follow but she does have weboption which helps a lot. I recommend going to her lecture and take notes then watch weboption to understand everything. She makes sense when you re-watch the lecture. She's a nice lady but cannot teach that well. Midterm was hard but final was easier. She also curved the class in the end.

TBH, you have to work for it. Its not like high school math where you just study the night before. Her test need at least 2 weeks prep. One week understanding the concepts and a week of practice and reviewing the concept. I learned everything from youtube channel called patrickjmt. The guy explains everything. Do the homework and practice.

No point in going to her lectures other than to copy down the notes she writes. You'll learn nothing because she doesn't explain concepts well. Her lectures are incredibly boring and you're better of reading the textbook and self-teaching.

nice teacher thats will help you understand the concepts, which will definately help you pass calc

rComments: Very helpful teacher! Highly recommend attending lectures regularly to avoid falling behind. Do the WebAssign option, it forces you to practice math. Tutorial instructors are a hit or miss. I did the full year course as its slower and offers more study time. I'm sure the semester course is doable, just be responsible about your studying.
She goes really fast and doesnt explain what she is doing or why.
She was very thorough and well organized. Loved her enthusiasm so early in the morning. SHe was VERY helpful in answering all the questions in lectures and in math aid hours.

While I did end up with a high mark in this course, I would strongly recommend prospective students to choose a different professor. The earlier posts are quite misleading, specifically those praising Professor Chrysostomou's teaching as I had found great difficulty in understanding what was taught in class. Avoid if possible!

Not the greatest prof by a mile. She had really bad notes that didnt print properly half the time, and were missing pages, made lots of mistakes in class, referred to all the online work but nothing in the textbook. She is really nice, and helpful, but she can't really relate the material all that well.

She is very helpful, good notes and lectures. She has an accent but its not a big problem. She cares for her students a lot, provides us with seminars that are VERY helpful!Remember 10 integrals a day keeps the bad marks away!
Fair, clear, lectures are a bit dry sometimes. Very approachable. You will do well if you keep up with all of the homework and lectures. No slacking. Tests will have you pressed for time.
Extremely hard and she complicates things that were already simple.
She's awesome!
she's a good prof.
Great professor, her teaching is very clear and her notes are very helpful. You HAVE to attend lectures for a good understanding, and tutorials really help as well.
Good prof
Great examples, well organized, good humor, answers emails promptly
Shes an awesome prof, the midterm was easy and I was getting a high 90 in the course, but the final was a killer!! practically impossible to pass :/
A thick accent, but nothing hindering the learning experience. Overall, a good professor, but the workload can sometimes get overbearing.
Extremely helpful and really fair with her tests and exams.

I was pretty confident going into math after doing well in high school calc. But this class has A LOT of workload and unless its manditory for you to take I suggest DONT take it! Made me switch my program of study because of this course. If you do bad in midterm, less than 40% then drop it.

Mata30: pretty fair/easy. Mata36: hard prof. Midterms and finals where very hard to make sure most people do bad, though she might bellcurve up slightly in the end (3-4%). Good notes, good examples, and good in everything else.
Extremely well organized, loves what she does, and gives great examples. If all math teachers were like her, math would have been the most liked course.

Sophie is friendly and pleasant. She welcomes in-lecture questions, and makes sure to address them. She makes lecture notes available to students, usually in a very clear form. Her accent is fairly thick but easy to understand. Her writing in class is mostly clear, but it is sometimes difficult to distinguish between some pairs of letters.

Chrysostomou is one of the more professional professors at the campus. Posts notes up already, so all you need to do is write the solutions to the examples she gives right on the printed notes which is extremely helpful. She is probably one of the best profs in the campus, ask her a lot of questions. She is not shy to help!!
Extremely good prof .. Makes Math more interesting. Her finals are pretty hard, but overall she is a perfect Math teacher.

She's a pretty good professor. Very, very organized and it helps students stay organized as well. The course material is difficult to begin with and moves very fast. The problem isn't really her at all, but the workload is a LOT so try to keep up from the beginning! Final is hard!
she is the best professor. i wish she was in my high school teacher!!
Sophie is a very helpful prof! She is really good at explaining concepts and very approachable.
best prof that I had so far

Chrysostomou is the best math teacher i've ever met. She is very organized and clear in her notes. Attending tutorials help a lot especially if taught by her too because she is so helpful and give one-to-one instruction. She is very approachable. She's the best!
